                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="acheson_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">(1893-1971) a US <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/diplomat#diplomat_topg_1" title="diplomat definition"><span class="ndv">diplomat</span></a> . He directed the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-marshall-plan#the_marshall_plan_topg_1" title="Marshall Plan definition"><span class="ndv">Marshall Plan</span></a> to help Europe after World War II and, as <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/secretary-of-state#secretaryofstate_sng_2" title="Secretary of State definition"><span class="ndv">Secretary of State</span></a> under President <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/harry-s-truman" title="Truman definition"><span class="ndv">Truman</span></a>, helped in 1949 to create the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/nato" title="North Atlantic Treaty Organization definition"><span class="ndv">North Atlantic Treaty Organization</span></a>. He received a <span class="ndv" href="pulitzerprize_d_1" xt="andv" tofix="">Pulitzer Prize</span> in 1970 for his book <span class="ebi">Present at the Creation: My Years in the State Department</span>.<span class="blockquote"><span class="p-g"><span class="wrap_open">“</span><span class="p">Great Britain has lost an empire and has not yet found a role.</span><span class="wrap_close">”</span></span><span class="footer">Dean Acheson 1962</span></span></span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
